│ 149 /// In what follows, the term "input IR" refers to code that is fed into    │
│ the                                                                             │
│ 150 /// vectorizer whereas the term "output IR" refers to code that is          │
│ generated by                                                                    │
│ 151 /// the vectorizer.                                                         │
│ 152                                                                             │
│ 153 /// VPLane provides a way to access lanes in both fixed width and scalable  │
│ 154 /// vectors, where for the latter the lane index sometimes needs            │
│ calculating                                                                     │
